HWHelloRange.description: The range of intervals on which hello messages are exchanged.
HWHelloRange.name: HWHelloRange

HWOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc.description: The range, in seconds, of dead interval value.
HWOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc.name: HWOspfv3DeadIntRangeTc

HWOspfv3LsIdTC.description: A unique 32-bit identifier of the piece of the routing domain that is being described by a link state advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the Link State ID (LSID) has no addressing semantics.
HWOspfv3LsIdTC.name: HWOspfv3LsIdTC
HWOspfv3LsIdTC.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.4, Link State ID

HWOspfv3LsaAgeTC.description: The age of the link state advertisement in seconds. The high-order bit of the LS age field is considered the DoNotAge bit for support of on-demand circuits.
HWOspfv3LsaAgeTC.name: HWOspfv3LsaAgeTC
HWOspfv3LsaAgeTC.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.1, LS age; Extending OSPF to Support Demand Circuits, Section 2.2, The LS age field

HWOspfv3LsaSequenceTC.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.
HWOspfv3LsaSequenceTC.name: HWOspfv3LsaSequenceTC
HWOspfv3LsaSequenceTC.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6, LS sequence number

HWOspfv3RouterIdTc.description: A 32-bit, unsigned integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses if IPv4 is configured on the router.
HWOspfv3RouterIdTc.name: HWOspfv3RouterIdTc

HWOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc.description: The values one might be able to configure for variables bounded by the Refresh Interval
HWOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc.name: HWOspfv3UpToRefreshIntervalTc

hwOspfv3.name: hwOspfv3

revisions.description: Added hwOspfv3IntraAreaRouterIdConflictRecovered to indicates the routerid conflict recovered
Initial version, published as RFC xxxx

hwOspfv3AdminStatus.description: The administrative status of OSPFv3 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPFv3 Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.
hwOspfv3AdminStatus.name: hwOspfv3AdminStatus

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaId.description: The Area the Address Aggregate is to be found within.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaId.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaId
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.description: The type of the Address Aggregate. This field specifies the Area Lsdb type that this Address Aggregate applies to.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateAreaLsdbType.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix A.4.1 The Link State Advertisement header

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.description: Prefixes subsumed by ranges either trigger the advertisement of the indicated aggregate (advertiseMatching), or result in the prefix not being advertised at all outside the area.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEffect

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range subsumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup.description: These area aggregate objects used required for aggregating OSPFv3 prefixes for summarization across areas.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateGroup

hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix
hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefix.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.description: The length of the prefix (in bits). A prefix can not be shorter than 0 bits.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength
hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixLength.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.description: The prefix type of ospfv3AreaAggregatePrefix. Only IPv6 addresses are expected.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregatePrefixType

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateRowStatus

hwOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.description: A range of IPv6 prefixes specified by a prefix/prefix length pair. Note that if ranges are configured such that one range subsumes another range the most specific match is the preferred one.
hwOspfv3AreaAggregateTable.name: hwOspfv3AreaAggregateTable

hwOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of Autonomous System border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.
hwOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount.name: hwOspfv3AreaAsBdrRtrCount

hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.description: The total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.
hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount.name: hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrCount

hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is an area border router.
hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.name: hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus
hwOspfv3AreaBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3 Splitting the AS into Areas

hwOspfv3AreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.
hwOspfv3AreaEntry.name: hwOspfv3AreaEntry

hwOspfv3AreaGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems supporting areas.
hwOspfv3AreaGroup.name: hwOspfv3AreaGroup

hwOspfv3AreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.
hwOspfv3AreaId.name: hwOspfv3AreaId
hwOspfv3AreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaIdIndex.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.
hwOspfv3AreaIdIndex.name: hwOspfv3AreaIdIndex

hwOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.description: Indicates whether an area is a Stub area, NSSA, or standard area. AS-scope LSAs are not imported into Stub Areas or NSSAs. NSSAs import AS-External data as NSSA LSAs which have Area-scope
hwOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.name: hwOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern
hwOspfv3AreaImportAsExtern.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAdvertisement

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAge.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAge

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.description: The 32-bit identifier of the Area from which the LSA was received.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbChecksum

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.description: A single Area-Scope Link State Advertisement.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbEntry

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that display their Area-scope link state database.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbGroup

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbLsId.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbLsId.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbLsId

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Area-Scope Link State Database.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTable.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTable

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Area-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbType.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbType

hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.
hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown.name: hwOspfv3AreaLsdbTypeKnown

hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.description: Indicates the number of Translator state changes that have occurred since the last start-up of the OSPFv3 routing process. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system and at other times as indicated by the value of ospfv3DiscontinuityTime.
hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents.name: hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorEvents

hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Indicates an NSSA border router's policy to perform NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs.
hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole

hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval.description: The stability interval defined as the number of seconds after an elected translator determines its services are no longer required that it should continue to perform its translation duties.
hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval.name: hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorStabInterval

hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.description: Indicates if and how an NSSA border router is performing NSSA translation of NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs. When this object is set to 'enabled', the NSSA border router's ospfv3AreaNssaTranslatorRole has been set to 'always'. When this object is set to 'elected', a candidate NSSA border router is translating NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs. When this object is set to 'disabled', a candidate NSSA Border router is NOT translating NSSA-LSAs into AS-External-LSAs.
hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState.name: hwOspfv3AreaNssaTranslatorState

hwOspfv3AreaRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.
hwOspfv3AreaRowStatus.name: hwOspfv3AreaRowStatus

hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Area-Scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.
hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum.name: hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCksumSum

hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Area-Scope link state advertisements in this area's link state database.
hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount.name: hwOspfv3AreaScopeLsaCount

hwOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.description: The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.
hwOspfv3AreaSpfRuns.name: hwOspfv3AreaSpfRuns

hwOspfv3AreaStubMetric.description: The metric value advertised for the default route into Stub and NSSA areas.
hwOspfv3AreaStubMetric.name: hwOspfv3AreaStubMetric

hwOspfv3AreaSummary.description: The variable ospfv3AreaSummary controls the import of Inter-Area LSAs into stub and NSSA areas. It has no effect on other areas. If it is noAreaSummary, the router will neither originate nor propagate Inter-Area LSAs into the stub or NSSA area. It will rely entirely on its default route. If it is sendAreaSummary, the router will both summarize and propagate Inter-Area LSAs.
hwOspfv3AreaSummary.name: hwOspfv3AreaSummary

hwOspfv3AreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.
hwOspfv3AreaTable.name: hwOspfv3AreaTable
hwOspfv3AreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Structure

hwOspfv3AsBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is configured as an Autonomous System border router.
hwOspfv3AsBdrRtrStatus.name: hwOspfv3AsBdrRtrStatus
hwOspfv3AsBdrRtrStatus.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 3.3 Classification of routers

hwOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbAdvertisement

hwOspfv3AsLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbAge.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbAge

hwOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbChecksum

hwOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.description: A single AS-Scope Link State Advertisement.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbEntry.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbEntry

hwOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that display their AS-scope link state database.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbGroup.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbGroup

hwOspfv3AsLsdbLsId.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbLsId.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbLsId

hwOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId
hwOspfv3AsLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters

hwOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbSequence
hwOspfv3AsLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number

hwOspfv3AsLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's AS-Scope Link State Database.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbTable.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbTable

hwOspfv3AsLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. AS-Scope LSAs not recognized by the router may be stored in the database.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbType.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbType

hwOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.
hwOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown.name: hwOspfv3AsLsdbTypeKnown

hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the LS checksums of the AS-scoped link state advertisements contained in the link state database. This sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.
hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum.name: hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCksumSum

hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.description: The number of AS-Scope (e.g. AS-External) link state advertisements in the link state database.
hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount.name: hwOspfv3AsScopeLsaCount

hwOspfv3AuthSequenceNumWrap.description: An hwOspfv3AuthSequenceNumWrap notification indicates that the 64-bit authentication sequence number has wrapped. When this notification is received, all the keys must be reset to avoid the possibility of replay attacks.
hwOspfv3AuthSequenceNumWrap.name: hwOspfv3AuthSequenceNumWrap

hwOspfv3BasicGroup.description: These objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 global parameters.
hwOspfv3BasicGroup.name: hwOspfv3BasicGroup

hwOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single configured neighbor or neighbor discovered by lower-level protocols such as Inverse Neighbor Discovery.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrEntry
hwOspfv3CfgNbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure

hwOspfv3CfgNbrGroup.description: These configured neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 configured neighbors.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrGroup.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrGroup

hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfIndex

hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrIfInstId

hwOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrPriority.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrPriority

hwOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrRowStatus

hwOspfv3CfgNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the static neighbor router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrRtrId.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrRtrId

hwOspfv3CfgNbrTable.description: A table of configured, non-virtual neighbor information.
hwOspfv3CfgNbrTable.name: hwOspfv3CfgNbrTable
hwOspfv3CfgNbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure

hwOspfv3ConfigErrorType.description: Potential types of configuration conflicts. Used by the ospfv3ConfigError and ospfv3ConfigVirtError notifications. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, this value pertaining to this object should be returned as noError
hwOspfv3ConfigErrorType.name: hwOspfv3ConfigErrorType

hwOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.description: The maximum number of non-default AS-external-LSAs entries that can be stored in the link state database. If the value is -1, then there is no limit. When the number of non-default AS-external-LSAs in a router's link-state database reaches ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit, the router enters Overflow state. The router never holds more than ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit non-default AS-external-LSAs in its database. Ospfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit MUST be set identically in all routers attached to the OSPFv3 backbone and/or any regular OSPFv3 area. (i.e., OSPFv3 stub areas and NSSAs are excluded).
hwOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit.name: hwOspfv3ExtAreaLsdbLimit

hwOspfv3ExtLsaCount.description: The number of AS-Scope External(LS type 0x4005) link state advertisements in the link state database
hwOspfv3ExtLsaCount.name: hwOspfv3ExtLsaCount

hwOspfv3IfAdminStatus.description: The OSPFv3 interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPFv3.
hwOspfv3IfAdminStatus.name: hwOspfv3IfAdminStatus

hwOspfv3IfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0 is used for the OSPFv3 backbone.
hwOspfv3IfAreaId.name: hwOspfv3IfAreaId

hwOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Backup Designated Router.
hwOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: hwOspfv3IfBackupDesignatedRouter

hwOspfv3IfConfigError.description: An ospfv3IfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.
hwOspfv3IfConfigError.name: hwOspfv3IfConfigError

hwOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.description: The Router ID of the Designated Router.
hwOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter.name: hwOspfv3IfDesignatedRouter

hwOspfv3IfEntry.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.
hwOspfv3IfEntry.name: hwOspfv3IfEntry

hwOspfv3IfEvents.description: The number of times this OSPFv3 interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.
hwOspfv3IfEvents.name: hwOspfv3IfEvents

hwOspfv3IfGroup.description: These interface objects used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 interfaces.
hwOspfv3IfGroup.name: hwOspfv3IfGroup

hwOspfv3IfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.
hwOspfv3IfHelloInterval.name: hwOspfv3IfHelloInterval

hwOspfv3IfIndex.description: The interface index of this OSPFv3 interface. It corresponds to the interface index of the IPv6 interface on which OSPFv3 is configured.
hwOspfv3IfIndex.name: hwOspfv3IfIndex

hwOspfv3IfInstId.description: Enables multiple interface instances of OSPFv3 to be run over a single link. Each protocol instance would be assigned a separate ID. This ID has local link significance only.
hwOspfv3IfInstId.name: hwOspfv3IfInstId

hwOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this link's link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.
hwOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: hwOspfv3IfLinkLsaCksumSum

hwOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link state advertisements in this link's link state database.
hwOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: hwOspfv3IfLinkScopeLsaCount

hwOspfv3IfMetricValue.description: The metric assigned to this interface. The default value of the Metric is Reference Bandwidth / ifSpeed. The value of the reference bandwidth is configured by the ospfv3ReferenceBandwidth object.
hwOspfv3IfMetricValue.name: hwOspfv3IfMetricValue

hwOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.description: The way multicasts should forwarded on this interface; not forwarded, forwarded as data link multicasts, or forwarded as data link unicasts. Data link multicasting is not meaningful on point to point and NBMA interfaces, and setting ospfv3MulticastForwarding to 0 effectively disables all multicast forwarding.
hwOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding.name: hwOspfv3IfMulticastForwarding

hwOspfv3IfPollInterval.description: The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi-access neighbor.
hwOspfv3IfPollInterval.name: hwOspfv3IfPollInterval

hwOspfv3IfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link state request packets.
hwOspfv3IfRetransInterval.name: hwOspfv3IfRetransInterval

hwOspfv3IfRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.
hwOspfv3IfRowStatus.name: hwOspfv3IfRowStatus

hwOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down on the interface. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.
hwOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval.name: hwOspfv3IfRtrDeadInterval

hwOspfv3IfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.
hwOspfv3IfRtrPriority.name: hwOspfv3IfRtrPriority

hwOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfv3IfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an OSPFv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a non-virtual interface.
hwOspfv3IfRxBadPacket.name: hwOspfv3IfRxBadPacket

hwOspfv3IfStateChange.description: An ospfv3IfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Dr to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point, DR Other, Dr, or Backup).
hwOspfv3IfStateChange.name: hwOspfv3IfStateChange

hwOspfv3IfTable.description: The OSPFv3 Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPFv3.
hwOspfv3IfTable.name: hwOspfv3IfTable
hwOspfv3IfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters

hwOspfv3IfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.
hwOspfv3IfTransitDelay.name: hwOspfv3IfTransitDelay

hwOspfv3IntraAreaRouterIdConflictRecover.description: The object is used to monitor router ID conflict recovery in an intra area.
hwOspfv3IntraAreaRouterIdConflictRecover.name: hwOspfv3IntraAreaRouterIdConflictRecovered

hwOspfv3LastAuthKeyExpiry.description: An hwOspfv3LastAuthKeyExpiry notification indicates that the last key associated with an interface has expired. When this notification is received, either the lifetime of the key should be extended or a new key should be configured.
hwOspfv3LastAuthKeyExpiry.name: hwOspfv3LastAuthKeyExpiry

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.description: The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAdvertisement

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAge.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbAge

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbChecksum

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.description: A single Link-Scope Link State Advertisement.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbEntry

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.description: These objects are used for OSPFv3 systems that display their Link-scope link state database.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbGroup

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.description: The identifier of the link from which the LSA was received.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfIndex

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.description: The identifier of the interface instance from which the LSA was received.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbIfInstId

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbLsId.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a unique identifier; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement. In contrast to OSPFv2, the LSID has no addressing semantics.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbLsId.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbLsId

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.description: The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbRouterId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.1 Global parameters

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbSequence.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 12.1.6 LS sequence number

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.description: The OSPFv3 Process's Link-Scope Link State Database.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTable.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTable

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format. Link-Scope LSAs unrecognized by the router are also stored in this database.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbType.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbType

hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.description: Indicates whether the LSA type is recognized by this Router.
hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown.name: hwOspfv3LinkLsdbTypeKnown

hwOspfv3NbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address of the neighbor associated with the local link.
hwOspfv3NbrAddress.name: hwOspfv3NbrAddress

hwOspfv3NbrAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3NbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.
hwOspfv3NbrAddressType.name: hwOspfv3NbrAddressType

hwOspfv3NbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor.
hwOspfv3NbrEntry.name: hwOspfv3NbrEntry
hwOspfv3NbrEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure

hwOspfv3NbrEvents.description: The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.
hwOspfv3NbrEvents.name: hwOspfv3NbrEvents

hwOspfv3NbrGroup.description: These neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 neighbors.
hwOspfv3NbrGroup.name: hwOspfv3NbrGroup

hwOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor
hwOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed.name: hwOspfv3NbrHelloSuppressed

hwOspfv3NbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this link, that is, the neighbor's local interface index.
hwOspfv3NbrIfId.name: hwOspfv3NbrIfId

hwOspfv3NbrIfIndex.description: The local link ID of the link over which the neighbor can be reached.
hwOspfv3NbrIfIndex.name: hwOspfv3NbrIfIndex

hwOspfv3NbrIfInstId.description: Interface instance over which the neighbor can be reached. This ID has local link significance only.
hwOspfv3NbrIfInstId.name: hwOspfv3NbrIfInstId

hwOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.
hwOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen.name: hwOspfv3NbrLsRetransQLen

hwOspfv3NbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.
hwOspfv3NbrOptions.name: hwOspfv3NbrOptions
hwOspfv3NbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field

hwOspfv3NbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.
hwOspfv3NbrPriority.name: hwOspfv3NbrPriority

hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPFv3 Graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.
hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge.name: hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperAge

hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currently underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.
hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc.name: hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperExitRc

hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor.
hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus.name: hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatus

hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.description: An ospfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor restart helper status transitions for a neighbor.
hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange.name: hwOspfv3NbrRestartHelperStatusChange

hwOspfv3NbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3NbrRtrId.name: hwOspfv3NbrRtrId

hwOspfv3NbrState.description: The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.
hwOspfv3NbrState.name: hwOspfv3NbrState

hwOspfv3NbrStateChange.description: An ospfv3NbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPFv3 neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., 2-Way or Full). When an neighbor transitions from or to Full on non-broadcast multi-access and broadcast networks, the notification should be generated by the designated router. A designated router transitioning to Down will be noted by ospfIfStateChange.
hwOspfv3NbrStateChange.name: hwOspfv3NbrStateChange

hwOspfv3NbrTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information.
hwOspfv3NbrTable.name: hwOspfv3NbrTable
hwOspfv3NbrTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 10 The Neighbor Data Structure

hwOspfv3NewRouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses, represented as a 32-bit unsigned integer, if IPv4 is configured on the router.
hwOspfv3NewRouterId.name: hwOspfv3NewRouterId

hwOspfv3NotificationEnable.description: If this object is set to true(1), then it enables the generation of OSPFv3 Notifications. If it is set to false(2), these notifications are not generated. Configured values MUST survive an agent reboot.
hwOspfv3NotificationEnable.name: hwOspfv3NotificationEnable

hwOspfv3NotificationGroup.description: This group is used for OSPFv3 notifications
hwOspfv3NotificationGroup.name: hwOspfv3NotificationGroup

hwOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup.description: These objects are used to record notification parameters
hwOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup.name: hwOspfv3NotificationObjectGroup

hwOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.description: An ospfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange notification indicates that there has been a change in the router's ability to translate OSPFv3 NSSA LSAs into OSPFv3 External LSAs. This notification should be generated when the Translator Status transitions from or to any defined status on a per area basis.
hwOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange.name: hwOspfv3NssaTranslatorStatusChange

hwOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.description: The number of new link-state advertisements that have been originated. This number is incremented each time the router originates a new LSA.
hwOspfv3OriginateNewLsas.name: hwOspfv3OriginateNewLsas

hwOspfv3PacketSrc.description: The IPv6 address of an inbound packet that cannot be identified by a neighbor instance. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, the value pertaining to this object should be returned as 0. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.
hwOspfv3PacketSrc.name: hwOspfv3PacketSrc

hwOspfv3PacketType.description: OSPFv3 packet types. When the last value of a notification using this object is needed, but no notifications of that type have been sent, the value pertaining to this object should be returned as nullPacket
hwOspfv3PacketType.name: hwOspfv3PacketType

hwOspfv3ProcessId.description: The process ID indicates the OSPFv3 process number. The value ranges from 1 to 65535.
hwOspfv3ProcessId.name: hwOspfv3ProcessId

hwOspfv3ReadOnlyCompliance.description: When this MIB module is implemented without support for read-create (i.e., in read-only mode), the implementation can claim read-only compliance. Such a device can then be monitored, but cannot be configured with this MIB.
hwOspfv3ReadOnlyCompliance.name: hwOspfv3ReadOnlyCompliance

hwOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.description: Reference bandwidth in kilobits per second for calculating default interface metrics. The default value is 100,000 KBPS (100 MBPS). This object is persistent, and when written, the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.
hwOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth.name: hwOspfv3ReferenceBandwidth

hwOspfv3RestartAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPFv3 Graceful restart interval.
hwOspfv3RestartAge.name: hwOspfv3RestartAge

hwOspfv3RestartExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at a Graceful restart. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currently underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.
hwOspfv3RestartExitRc.name: hwOspfv3RestartExitRc

hwOspfv3RestartInterval.description: Configured OSPFv3 Graceful restart timeout interval.
hwOspfv3RestartInterval.name: hwOspfv3RestartInterval

hwOspfv3RestartStatus.description: The current status of OSPFv3 Graceful restart capability.
hwOspfv3RestartStatus.name: hwOspfv3RestartStatus

hwOspfv3RestartStatusChange.description: An ospfv3RestartStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart state for the router. This notification should be generated when the router restart status changes.
hwOspfv3RestartStatusChange.name: hwOspfv3RestartStatusChange

hwOspfv3RestartSupport.description: The router's support for OSPFv3 Graceful restart. Options include: no restart support, only planned restarts or both planned and unplanned restarts.
hwOspfv3RestartSupport.name: hwOspfv3RestartSupport

hwOspfv3RouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. To ensure uniqueness, this may default to the value of one of the router's IPv4 host addresses, represented as a 32-bit unsigned integer, if IPv4 is configured on the router.
hwOspfv3RouterId.name: hwOspfv3RouterId

hwOspfv3RxNewLsas.description: The number of link state advertisements received determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated link state advertisements.
hwOspfv3RxNewLsas.name: hwOspfv3RxNewLsas

hwOspfv3VersionNumber.description: The version number of OSPF for IPv6 is 3.
hwOspfv3VersionNumber.name: hwOspfv3VersionNumber

hwOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.description: The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not Area 0
hwOspfv3VirtIfAreaId.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfAreaId

hwOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.description: An ospfv3VirtIfConfigError notification signifies that a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a notification only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.
hwOspfv3VirtIfConfigError.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfConfigError

hwOspfv3VirtIfEntry.description: Information about a single Virtual Interface.
hwOspfv3VirtIfEntry.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfEntry

hwOspfv3VirtIfEvents.description: The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link
hwOspfv3VirtIfEvents.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfEvents

hwOspfv3VirtIfGroup.description: These virtual interface objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 virtual interfaces.
hwOspfv3VirtIfGroup.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfGroup

hwOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfHelloInterval

hwOspfv3VirtIfIndex.description: The local interface index assigned to this OSPFv3 virtual interface. It is advertised in Hello's sent over the virtual link and in the router's router-LSAs.
hwOspfv3VirtIfIndex.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfIndex

hwOspfv3VirtIfInstId.description: Specifies the interface instance ID to be used for the virtual interface. This ID has local link significance only.
hwOspfv3VirtIfInstId.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfInstId

hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the Link-Scope link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this virtual link's link-state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link state database of two routers.
hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkLsaCksumSum

hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.description: The total number of Link-Scope link state advertisements in this virtual link's link state database.
hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfLinkScopeLsaCount

hwOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfNeighbor

hwOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip time.
hwOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfRetransInterval

hwOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.
hwOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfRowStatus

hwOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfRtrDeadInterval

hwOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket notification signifies that an OSPFv3 packet that cannot be parsed has been received on a virtual interface.
hwOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfRxBadPacket

hwOspfv3VirtIfState.description: OSPFv3 virtual interface states. The same encoding as the hwOspfv3IfTable is used.
hwOspfv3VirtIfState.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfState

hwOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.description: An ospfv3VirtIfStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual interface. This notification should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Point-to-Point to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point).
hwOspfv3VirtIfStateChange.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfStateChange

hwOspfv3VirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual interfaces.
hwOspfv3VirtIfTable.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfTable
hwOspfv3VirtIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.4 Virtual link parameters

hwOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface.
hwOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay.name: hwOspfv3VirtIfTransitDelay

hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.description: The IPv6 address advertised by this Virtual Neighbor. It must be a Global scope address.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddress.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddress

hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.description: The address type of ospfv3VirtNbrAddress. Only IPv6 addresses without zone index are expected.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrAddressType

hwOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.description: The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrEvents.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrEvents

hwOspfv3VirtNbrGroup.description: These virtual neighbor objects are used for managing/monitoring OSPFv3 virtual neighbors.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrGroup.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrGroup

hwOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.description: Indicates whether Hellos are being suppressed to the neighbor
hwOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrHelloSuppressed

hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.description: The interface ID that the neighbor advertises in its Hello Packets on this virtual link, that is, the neighbor's local interface ID.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfId.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfId

hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.description: The local interface ID for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfIndex

hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.description: The interface instance for the virtual link over which the neighbor can be reached.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrIfInstId

hwOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.description: The current length of the retransmission queue.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrLsRetransQLen

hwOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.description: A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrOptions
hwOspfv3VirtNbrOptions.reference: OSPF Version 3, Appendix A.2 the Options field

hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPFv3 Graceful restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperAge

hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor. none:............no restart has yet been attempted. inProgress:......a restart attempt is currently underway. completed:.......the last restart completed successfully. timedOut:........the last restart timed out. topologyChanged:.the last restart was aborted due to a topology change.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperExitRc

hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a Graceful restart helper for the neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatus

hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange.description: An ospfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the graceful restart helper state for the virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the virtual neighbor restart helper status transitions for a virtual neighbor.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrRestartHelperStatusChange

hwOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrRtrId

hwOspfv3VirtNbrState.description: The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relationship.
hwOspfv3VirtNbrState.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrState

hwOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.description: An ospfv3VirtNbrStateChange notification signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPFv3 virtual neighbor. This notification should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., Full).
hwOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange.name: hwOspfv3VirtNbrStateChange
